# Routing Structure

Pablo uses SvelteKit's file-based routing system. The main routes are:

## Main Pages

- [src/routes/+page.svelte](mdc:src/routes/+page.svelte) - Landing page with features, testimonials, and marketing information
- [src/routes/new/+page.svelte](mdc:src/routes/new/+page.svelte) - Design creation interface with artboard and AI assistant
- [src/routes/design/+page.svelte](mdc:src/routes/design/+page.svelte) - Experimental canvas using svelte-konva for design manipulation

## API Routes

- [src/routes/api/generate-design/+server.ts](mdc:src/routes/api/generate-design/+server.ts) - Design generation endpoint

The application follows SvelteKit's routing conventions:
- `+page.svelte` files define page components
- `+layout.svelte` files define layouts that wrap page components
- `+server.ts` files define API endpoints